<h2>C-Tier Swords (Situational)</h2>
<ul><li><strong>Cutlass</strong> – Starter sword, replace ASAP.</li>
<li><strong>Katana</strong> – Basic, outclassed by almost everything.</li>
<li><strong>Dual Katana</strong> – Decent early game, but not worth upgrading.</li></ul>

<h2>Best Sword for Each Playstyle</h2>
<ul><li><strong>Grinding:</strong> Shark Saw (best AOE) → Saber V2 (early game).</li>
<li><strong>PvP:</strong> Dark Dagger (speed) → Koko (damage) → Rengoku (reach).</li>
<li><strong>Boss Fights:</strong> Triple Katana (DPS) → Dragon Trident (range).</li>
<li><strong>Sea Events:</strong> Shark Saw (AOE) → Dragon Trident (reach).</li></ul>

<h2>How to Get Swords Fast</h2>
<ol><li><strong>Saber V2</strong> – Complete the Saber Expert quest in First Sea (easiest S-Tier).</li>
<li><strong>Shark Saw</strong> – Complete Sharkman quest in Second Sea (best grinding sword).</li>
<li><strong>Dark Dagger</strong> – Save 100 Bones from killing NPCs (best PvP sword).</li>
<li><strong>Triple Katana</strong> – Complete the hidden quest in Third Sea (best DPS).</li></ol>

<h2>Sword Combos (PvP)</h2>
<ul><li><strong>Dark Dagger + Godhuman:</strong> C (DD) → Z (DD) → Godhuman C → X (DD) → Finisher</li>
<li><strong>Koko + Electric Claw:</strong> Z (Koko) → Electric Claw C → X (Koko) → Finisher</li>
<li><strong>Saber V2 + Buddha:</strong> Z (Saber) → Buddha C → X (Saber) → Buddha X → Finisher</li></ul>

<h2>Pro Tips</h2>
<ul><li><strong>Focus on Shark Saw first</strong> – it's the best sword for grinding, which is your priority early on.</li>
<li><strong>Dark Dagger is worth the grind</strong> – 100 Bones is not that much, and it's the best PvP sword.</li>
<li><strong>Don't waste time on C-Tier swords</strong> – they're outclassed by everything else.</li>
<li><strong>Upgrade Saber V1 to V2 as soon as possible</strong> – it's a massive upgrade.</li>
<li><strong>If you PvP regularly</strong>, prioritize Dark Dagger or Koko – they're the meta.</li></ul>

